cs.HC, cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.MS, cs.SI

The paper describes a virtual reality framework for handling patient data in a surgical context. This involves the use of 3D data, imagery, and temporal data, which suggests that the paper could fall under several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

Firstly, cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a likely category as the paper discusses the use of VR technology to aid surgeons in processing patient data. 

Secondly, cs.GR (Graphics) is also a likely category as the paper describes the rendering of 3D patient data in stereo to increase depth perception. 

Thirdly, cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a possible category as the paper mentions the use of imagery in the framework. 

Fourthly, cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is a possible category as the paper describes the use of a modular design for the framework, which suggests the use of software engineering principles. 

Finally, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the paper discusses the organization of patient data into workspaces and the use of tools to control and manipulate the data, which could be seen as a form of information network.
